snippet: Exchanges report sharp rise in applications processed for private and public insurance.
abstract: Editorial welcomes news that the number of people signing up for health insurance plans under the Affordable Care Act has accelerated greatly, particularly for Medicaid programs for the poor; notes while enrollment has been slower than anticipated, it is surprisingly robust given the start-up troubles.
lead_paragraph: Exchanges report sharp rise in applications processed for private and public insurance.
